00:13:25,409 --> 00:13:28,278
Next into the tank
is Michael J. Desanti

00:13:28,278 --> 00:13:30,647
with a product to discourage
little thieves.

00:13:30,647 --> 00:13:33,483
♪♪♪

00:13:35,719 --> 00:13:38,488
Hello, sharks.

00:13:41,491 --> 00:13:44,528
My Michael J. Desanti.
Mike D. for short.

00:13:44,528 --> 00:13:47,698
I am seeking $130,000
in exchange

00:13:47,698 --> 00:13:50,434
for 40% of my business.

00:13:50,434 --> 00:13:52,603
And my business is
the squirrel boss

00:13:52,603 --> 00:13:55,405
squirrel-proof bird feeder.

00:13:55,405 --> 00:13:59,176
(sharks laughing)

00:13:59,176 --> 00:14:00,477
Squirrel boss is
the world's first

00:14:00,477 --> 00:14:03,280
interactive squirrel-Proof
bird feeder.

00:14:03,280 --> 00:14:06,316
Now, we know squirrels
are extremely cute,

00:14:06,316 --> 00:14:08,185
and they need to eat, too.

00:14:08,185 --> 00:14:11,288
But they are 5-Pound gorillas,
and they are hogs!

00:14:11,288 --> 00:14:14,257
But with squirrel boss,

00:14:14,257 --> 00:14:15,626
if you see a squirrel
on your bird feeder,

00:14:15,626 --> 00:14:18,595
and he wears out
his welcome,

00:14:18,595 --> 00:14:20,597
just press the remote control

00:14:20,597 --> 00:14:23,367
and deliver a harmless
static-shock correction.

00:14:23,367 --> 00:14:24,668
(sharks laughing)

00:14:24,668 --> 00:14:27,270
That is similar
to walking across the carpet

00:14:27,270 --> 00:14:30,207
and touching something.
Buh-Bam! (laughs)

00:14:30,207 --> 00:14:32,275
It tingles,
but it doesn't hurt you.

00:14:32,275 --> 00:14:35,445
Who would like to challenge
the squirrel boss?

00:14:38,248 --> 00:14:40,384
Whoo! (laughs)
You are up!

00:14:40,384 --> 00:14:41,618
Please Come and grab
this squirrel boss.

00:14:41,618 --> 00:14:43,286
(Robert) Mike,
can I please zap her?

00:14:43,286 --> 00:14:44,621
You may.
(laughs)

00:14:44,621 --> 00:14:47,457
♪♪♪

00:14:47,457 --> 00:14:49,493
Go ahead.
Ready?

00:14:49,493 --> 00:14:52,362
Aah!
(laughter)

00:14:52,362 --> 00:14:54,531
You know what? I missed it.
Would you guys do it again?

00:14:54,531 --> 00:14:56,366
Hey, big shot,
why don't you try it?

00:14:56,366 --> 00:14:58,335
Yeah, come on, cuban!
(Lori) Yeah!

00:14:58,335 --> 00:15:00,137
What if there's two squirrels
on it?

00:15:00,137 --> 00:15:01,405
Okay. Ready?
That's fine.

00:15:01,405 --> 00:15:02,539
Two squirrels!
(zap)

00:15:02,539 --> 00:15:06,576
(laughter)

00:15:06,576 --> 00:15:09,179
It's... (speaks indistinctly)
Kaboom!

00:15:09,179 --> 00:15:10,347
Everybody!
Come--

00:15:10,347 --> 00:15:12,149
Okay, I gotta try it.
You must feel this.

00:15:14,117 --> 00:15:17,320
(laughs)

00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:19,189
I don't feel anything.

00:15:22,225 --> 00:15:23,527
(zap)
(high-pitched voice) Aah!

00:15:23,527 --> 00:15:25,328
(laughter)

00:15:25,328 --> 00:15:27,297
Daymond John, you are up!

00:15:28,432 --> 00:15:30,300
(zap)
Aah!

00:15:30,300 --> 00:15:32,369
(laughter)
(Lori) Come on, kev.

00:15:32,369 --> 00:15:35,272
No, thank you!

00:15:35,272 --> 00:15:37,174
(Robert) So, Mike--Mike D.,
just to be clear,

00:15:37,174 --> 00:15:38,375
I'm sitting in my house.
Yes.

00:15:38,375 --> 00:15:40,510
I see the little squirrel
eating.
Yes.

00:15:40,510 --> 00:15:43,246
I think he's had too much.
I zap him?

00:15:43,246 --> 00:15:44,381
That's the whole thing.

00:15:44,381 --> 00:15:45,515
When I said
"Wears out his welcome"--

00:15:45,515 --> 00:15:47,217
because squirrels need
to eat, too.

00:15:47,217 --> 00:15:49,119
But that means I have to be
watching the bird feed--

00:15:49,119 --> 00:15:50,587
That's
our second-Biggest objection

00:15:50,587 --> 00:15:53,523
that I get all of the time
in public and--

00:15:53,523 --> 00:15:55,158
What's the first?
That you have to be watching--

00:15:55,158 --> 00:15:57,260
It's too expensive,
and that's why I'm here.

00:15:57,260 --> 00:16:00,297
I have a question. Let's say
the squirrel, named Joe...

00:16:00,297 --> 00:16:02,432
(chuckles)
goes on, gets zapped.

00:16:02,432 --> 00:16:05,335
Does Joe then never
come back again?

00:16:05,335 --> 00:16:07,070
And how many shocks
can Joe take?

00:16:07,070 --> 00:16:08,371
No, excellent question,
Lori.

00:16:08,371 --> 00:16:11,274
Um... it gets Boring
really fast.

00:16:11,274 --> 00:16:13,343
Boring?
Boring, meaning he won't
touch it after two shocks.

00:16:13,343 --> 00:16:15,112
Oh, he won't touch it?
He won't touch it.

00:16:15,112 --> 00:16:17,114
But, Mike, wouldn't
the animal rights people

00:16:17,114 --> 00:16:18,448
get all over this?
You're el--

00:16:18,448 --> 00:16:21,184
You're electrocuting
the animals.

00:16:21,184 --> 00:16:23,086
Actually, they like it,

00:16:23,086 --> 00:16:25,522
because they know
the alternative is lethal force.

00:16:25,522 --> 00:16:29,259
People are, unfortunately,
shooting squirrels to death.

00:16:29,259 --> 00:16:31,094
There's no way to stop
an animal--

00:16:31,094 --> 00:16:33,096
Is that legal?
It's totally legal,

00:16:33,096 --> 00:16:34,397
totally unethical.

00:16:34,397 --> 00:16:37,434
There's a squirrel rehabilitator
in massachusetts.

00:16:37,434 --> 00:16:39,236
Squirrel rehabilitator?

00:16:39,236 --> 00:16:41,138
If he finds squirrels
that were orphaned,

00:16:41,138 --> 00:16:43,306
for whatever reason,
he'll nurse the baby squirrels

00:16:43,306 --> 00:16:45,375
with a bottle till they're
well enough to go away.
(laughs)

00:16:45,375 --> 00:16:47,210
And you know what?
He said to me--

00:16:47,210 --> 00:16:49,513
he said, "Mike D., I would not
own your bird feeder,

00:16:49,513 --> 00:16:52,349
but I like it, because I know
the alternative is terrible."

00:16:54,151 --> 00:16:56,052
Mike, is there
a business here?

00:16:56,052 --> 00:16:57,387
Tell--Tell me
the business side of it.

00:16:57,387 --> 00:16:59,156
Let's get serious here.
Okay.

00:16:59,156 --> 00:17:02,058
We have sold $196,096.

00:17:02,058 --> 00:17:05,162
It was 4,131 units.

00:17:05,162 --> 00:17:10,167
Average wholesale price--
$47.47 per Unit.

00:17:10,167 --> 00:17:12,202
How much money have you
put into it so far?

00:17:12,202 --> 00:17:13,336
I had an Angel investor.

00:17:13,336 --> 00:17:15,005
How much did he put in?

00:17:15,005 --> 00:17:16,106
$140,000.

00:17:16,106 --> 00:17:17,174
Really?

00:17:17,174 --> 00:17:18,175
How much have you
paid him back?

00:17:18,175 --> 00:17:19,376
All but $38,000.
Good for you.

00:17:19,376 --> 00:17:21,278
And I'd be in the black
right now,

00:17:21,278 --> 00:17:23,280
but we spent $60,000
on "Traditional marketing"

00:17:23,280 --> 00:17:24,381
That didn't work.

00:17:26,983 --> 00:17:29,252
Have you put up
any of your money?

00:17:29,252 --> 00:17:30,453
I--a lot of my money,
and...

00:17:30,453 --> 00:17:33,123
how much?

00:17:33,123 --> 00:17:35,091
Thousands.

00:17:35,091 --> 00:17:36,960
Not tens of thousands.

00:17:38,328 --> 00:17:40,397
Do you have a patent on it?

00:17:40,397 --> 00:17:43,066
Unfortunately, the--I had
the worst patent attorney

00:17:43,066 --> 00:17:45,035
on planet earth.
He was older than dirt.

00:17:45,035 --> 00:17:47,237
He was 15 years behind
the current state of the law,

00:17:47,237 --> 00:17:50,073
so it was denied.
We chose not to appeal--

00:17:50,073 --> 00:17:53,076
was it denied because something
else existed already like it?

00:17:53,076 --> 00:17:54,077
No, no, no.

00:17:54,077 --> 00:17:56,313
It says, "As seen on tv."

00:17:56,313 --> 00:17:58,148
Does that say that on there?

00:17:58,148 --> 00:18:00,083
It--it does, because
the news crew came to my house.

00:18:00,083 --> 00:18:02,986
So it was a news story
on tv.
Oh, so it's a quasi--

00:18:02,986 --> 00:18:05,322
(laughter)
It's not a real "As seen on Tv."

00:18:05,322 --> 00:18:08,091
Well, in business, you...
it's a--It's a--

00:18:08,091 --> 00:18:10,026
(laughter)
It's a imitation.

00:18:12,062 --> 00:18:14,030
♪♪♪

00:18:14,030 --> 00:18:15,999
(Robert) Mike,
here's my challenge with it.
Sure.

00:18:15,999 --> 00:18:18,201
I see it as a quirky product.
You'll sell some.

00:18:18,201 --> 00:18:20,036
You'll make a little bit
of money.

00:18:20,036 --> 00:18:22,172
But I wouldn't quit
my day job today.

00:18:22,172 --> 00:18:24,140
Good for you for inventing it,

00:18:24,140 --> 00:18:25,909
but, uh, I don't want
to get zapped again.

00:18:25,909 --> 00:18:28,044
I'm out.

00:18:28,044 --> 00:18:29,246
Well, thank you.
I appreciate that,

00:18:29,246 --> 00:18:30,947
but I strongly disagree.

00:18:30,947 --> 00:18:33,917
This, uh, pays for itself
with the seed you save.

00:18:33,917 --> 00:18:35,385
It's fun every time.

00:18:35,385 --> 00:18:39,222
It's saving the lives
of millions of squirrels.

00:18:39,222 --> 00:18:41,024
Mike, here's my thought.

00:18:41,024 --> 00:18:44,094
To me, to zap a squirrel--
That's a little sadistic.

00:18:45,328 --> 00:18:47,230
For that reason, I'm out.

00:18:49,232 --> 00:18:50,934
Guys, I really do need
a deal.

00:18:50,934 --> 00:18:52,335
I can't leave without a deal.
You know what, Mike?

00:18:52,335 --> 00:18:55,105
It's not a product that
I'm gonna put my heart into.

00:18:55,105 --> 00:18:58,108
I'm just not a squirrel
whisperer, so I'm out, Mike.

00:18:58,108 --> 00:19:00,310
I'm really sorry to hear that.

00:19:00,310 --> 00:19:02,212
(Kevin) This may shock you,
Mike.

00:19:03,880 --> 00:19:05,215
I'm out.

00:19:05,215 --> 00:19:07,918
I'm not shocked, but I
appreciate that. Thank you.

00:19:07,918 --> 00:19:09,853
So only Damon's left, I think.

00:19:09,853 --> 00:19:13,123
♪♪♪

00:19:15,158 --> 00:19:17,027
I'm out.

00:19:20,130 --> 00:19:21,932
I can't leave.

00:19:21,932 --> 00:19:23,166
I won't leave.

00:19:26,102 --> 00:19:27,170
You know what?
Put your hand on that.

00:19:27,170 --> 00:19:29,873
Give me that button.
You'll be gone soon.

00:19:29,873 --> 00:19:31,141
(sharks laughing)

00:19:31,141 --> 00:19:32,976
Okay. Thank you.
(Daymond)
Thank you so much.

00:19:32,976 --> 00:19:34,177
(Lori) Good luck.
Okay, have a good day.

00:19:34,177 --> 00:19:35,879
Good luck. You're very clever.

