to sell gumbo

00:30:09,904 --> 00:30:12,007
on the street corner,
and when we realized

00:30:12,007 --> 00:30:13,875
how popular it was,
we realized

00:30:13,875 --> 00:30:16,745
we have something
really good going.

00:30:16,745 --> 00:30:18,647
Don't forget
to say your prayers.

00:30:18,647 --> 00:30:20,115
I've sacrificed a lot
for this company.

00:30:20,115 --> 00:30:22,884
We've been through a lot
of struggles, my daughter and I.

00:30:22,884 --> 00:30:24,786
Financially, we've gone
through a lot

00:30:24,786 --> 00:30:25,920
where we didn't have
enough money

00:30:25,920 --> 00:30:27,689
just to make it
through the week.

00:30:27,689 --> 00:30:30,058
I've gotten a lot of interest
from a major grocery chain.

00:30:30,058 --> 00:30:32,027
They want to put my gumbo
in their stores,

00:30:32,027 --> 00:30:33,895
but I just don't have the funds
to produce the orders

00:30:33,895 --> 00:30:35,697
and Seal the deal.

00:30:35,697 --> 00:30:37,065
I hope the sharks
really do like gumbo.

00:30:37,065 --> 00:30:39,701
I hope they know
what good gumbo really is.

00:30:39,701 --> 00:30:41,870
I hope that they'll see
that it's a good product

00:30:41,870 --> 00:30:44,639
and they want to invest in it,
'cause we really need it.

00:30:46,775 --> 00:30:49,711
♪♪♪

00:30:59,688 --> 00:31:01,923
Hi. I'm Carole Foster,

00:31:01,923 --> 00:31:05,026
creator of Mee-Ma's
Louisiana gumbo bricks.

00:31:05,026 --> 00:31:07,696
I'm seeking $200,000
in exchange

00:31:07,696 --> 00:31:09,831
for 20% of my company.

00:31:09,831 --> 00:31:13,768
You know, good gumbo
is really hard to find,

00:31:13,768 --> 00:31:16,671
and so is the time it takes
to make it yourself.

00:31:16,671 --> 00:31:17,972
I've been
a long-Haul truck driver

00:31:17,972 --> 00:31:19,808
for the past 13 years,

00:31:19,808 --> 00:31:21,576
so I've tasted quite a bit
of gumbo

00:31:21,576 --> 00:31:22,811
throughout this country.

00:31:22,811 --> 00:31:26,915
Besides being a truck driver,
I am a total gumbo geek.

00:31:26,915 --> 00:31:30,051
A few years ago, friends asked
me to make gumbo for them

00:31:30,051 --> 00:31:32,887
for the holidays,
but each in a different way.

00:31:32,887 --> 00:31:34,689
And I just didn't have
time for that.

00:31:34,689 --> 00:31:37,025
Because even for
an experienced cook like myself,

00:31:37,025 --> 00:31:39,728
gumbo can take hours
to prepare.

00:31:39,728 --> 00:31:42,664
So instead,
I made for them a frozen,

00:31:42,664 --> 00:31:44,566
fully seasoned gumbo base

00:31:44,566 --> 00:31:46,568
that they could add
whatever they like to it.

00:31:46,568 --> 00:31:48,737
And so that's how Mee-Ma's
gumbo Bricks were born.

00:31:48,737 --> 00:31:50,905
Now, I'd love
to have you try

00:31:50,905 --> 00:31:52,974
some of the chicken
and seafood gumbo.

00:31:52,974 --> 00:31:54,676
Absolutely.
(Robert) I'd love to try.

00:31:56,878 --> 00:31:59,581
This one's seafood.
All right.
I'll try that one.

00:31:59,581 --> 00:32:00,849
Okay.

00:32:00,849 --> 00:32:02,917
I'll try the chicken.
That one's chicken.

00:32:02,917 --> 00:32:04,953
I love gumbo, Carole.
The seafood one
is in the front,

00:32:04,953 --> 00:32:06,554
chicken in the back.

00:32:06,554 --> 00:32:07,789
Okay, I'll try the Seafood.
Okay.

00:32:09,591 --> 00:32:10,992
(Robert) Ooh, it's got some
jalapeño kick in there.

00:32:10,992 --> 00:32:12,627
You taste that?
All right.

00:32:15,630 --> 00:32:17,699
It is delicious.

00:32:17,699 --> 00:32:18,800
Thank you.
It is very good.

00:32:18,800 --> 00:32:20,902
Who's ready to be
a gumbo geek like me?

00:32:20,902 --> 00:32:23,805
Carole, has that okra
been frozen, that I'm eating?

00:32:23,805 --> 00:32:25,640
That okra is frozen.

00:32:25,640 --> 00:32:27,575
Damn, that's good.
Yeah.

00:32:27,575 --> 00:32:28,843
That's really good.
And I want to say
to you,

00:32:28,843 --> 00:32:30,678
Mr. Wonderful...
Yeah.

00:32:30,678 --> 00:32:32,614
You are the okra
in my gumbo--

00:32:32,614 --> 00:32:33,815
Slimy though it may be,

00:32:33,815 --> 00:32:37,719
it adds character,
and it adds body,

00:32:37,719 --> 00:32:39,554
and it adds richness.
You're describing me.

00:32:39,554 --> 00:32:40,655
So--Exactly.

00:32:40,655 --> 00:32:41,923
That's why I love okra.
(laughs)

00:32:41,923 --> 00:32:43,958
I love it.
It's very tasty.
Exactly. All right.

00:32:43,958 --> 00:32:47,529
Carole, who's the lady
in the photo?

00:32:47,529 --> 00:32:49,464
That's my grandmother.
She lived to be 97.

00:32:49,464 --> 00:32:51,533
She's gone to glory now,
but she's the one

00:32:51,533 --> 00:32:52,901
who taught me
how to make gumbo.

00:32:52,901 --> 00:32:55,637
The recipe is really
inspired by her.

00:32:55,637 --> 00:32:57,605
When I buy the brick...
yes.

00:32:57,605 --> 00:32:59,674
Do I add more to it,

00:32:59,674 --> 00:33:02,510
or can I just
serve that up as is?

00:33:02,510 --> 00:33:04,813
No. This one allows you
to put what you like in it.

00:33:04,813 --> 00:33:06,815
So you've got the base?
This is the base.

00:33:06,815 --> 00:33:08,683
Could we see the packages?
Sure. Sure.

00:33:08,683 --> 00:33:10,518
What do I do
once I get the base, Carole?

00:33:10,518 --> 00:33:12,687
You're gonna add
6 to 8 cups of water

00:33:12,687 --> 00:33:14,522
to every gumbo brick...
thank you.

00:33:14,522 --> 00:33:17,759
And up to 5 pounds
of meat of your choice.

00:33:17,759 --> 00:33:20,929
And how long does it take
before I'm eating the gumbo?

00:33:20,929 --> 00:33:22,697
45 minutes or less.

00:33:22,697 --> 00:33:25,466
Carole, do you have sales
of your product today?

00:33:25,466 --> 00:33:26,568
Yes, I do.

00:33:26,568 --> 00:33:28,803
We've sold
gumbo bricks at the church.

00:33:28,803 --> 00:33:31,573
(Lori) Wow.
However, my latest success is,

00:33:31,573 --> 00:33:34,442
this has been selling
at various costcos in the area

00:33:34,442 --> 00:33:35,710
for the last two years,

00:33:35,710 --> 00:33:37,612
and I have about a half
a million dollars in sales.

00:33:37,612 --> 00:33:38,746
Wow.
In the last two years?

00:33:38,746 --> 00:33:41,816
Yes. But that's being
in one costco a week,

00:33:41,816 --> 00:33:43,718
for only three days a week.

00:33:43,718 --> 00:33:45,553
So you're setting up
and serving it

00:33:45,553 --> 00:33:47,856
and presenting it?
Right.
As a road show item.

00:33:47,856 --> 00:33:49,724
Right.
That's where
a lot of the money

00:33:49,724 --> 00:33:51,426
that we've generated

00:33:51,426 --> 00:33:52,660
over the last two
and a half years has gone to.

00:33:52,660 --> 00:33:55,463
Wow.
Sounds like you're doing great.

00:33:55,463 --> 00:33:57,365
Well...
you've gotten into costco.

00:33:57,365 --> 00:33:58,666
Mm-hmm.
You're selling
half a million a year.

00:33:58,666 --> 00:34:00,368
Yes.
What--what do you
need money for?

00:34:00,368 --> 00:34:02,370
We need money so that we can
increase our inventory

00:34:02,370 --> 00:34:04,539
and get it into more stores.

00:34:04,539 --> 00:34:08,710
I currently have
a, uh, buy doc from costco.

00:34:08,710 --> 00:34:12,480
(papers rustling)
and they are ready
and willing to accept

00:34:12,480 --> 00:34:15,383
15 pallets of product
right now.

00:34:15,383 --> 00:34:16,751
The problem--
15 pallets?

00:34:16,751 --> 00:34:18,553
Correct.
It's gonna have to
be frozen, though, right?

00:34:18,553 --> 00:34:20,521
It is frozen.
So is that
a permanent listing,

00:34:20,521 --> 00:34:22,624
or they're gonna put it...
they're gonna put it in
as a permanent item.

00:34:22,624 --> 00:34:24,759
As a matter of fact, we were
accepted as a permanent item

00:34:24,759 --> 00:34:27,662
earlier this year,
and our problem was,

00:34:27,662 --> 00:34:29,397
we couldn't keep up
with inventory.

00:34:29,397 --> 00:34:31,566
They wanted us
to keep that freezer full.

00:34:31,566 --> 00:34:32,800
We weren't able
to do that.
Congratulations.

00:34:32,800 --> 00:34:35,403
What a wonderful problem
you have.
(laughs) Exactly.

00:34:35,403 --> 00:34:38,439
Is that in costcos nationwide,
or is that in just a region?
No.

00:34:38,439 --> 00:34:39,641
Just in the region,
here in L.A.

00:34:39,641 --> 00:34:40,808
Can we see your order,

00:34:40,808 --> 00:34:42,810
that you had referenced?
Yes, absolutely.

00:34:42,810 --> 00:34:45,747
So, Carole,
you were in costco,

00:34:45,747 --> 00:34:48,383
and you were
giving out samples...
correct.

00:34:48,383 --> 00:34:51,419
And people were Loving it?
Yes. We sold 50,000 units.

00:34:51,419 --> 00:34:53,454
So do you think
that you would be able

00:34:53,454 --> 00:34:56,624
to get your gumbo
into the costcos nationwide?

00:34:56,624 --> 00:34:59,727
Yes. Costco has
about 600 clubs nationwide.

00:34:59,727 --> 00:35:01,396
Even if I were only able

00:35:01,396 --> 00:35:03,698
to get into
a third of those stores,

00:35:03,698 --> 00:35:05,667
the numbers
would be... incredible.

00:35:05,667 --> 00:35:07,435
Well, tell us
about your costs

00:35:07,435 --> 00:35:08,603
and what you're
selling them for.

00:35:08,603 --> 00:35:11,406
That gumbo brick
Costs about $4 to make.

00:35:11,406 --> 00:35:13,341
Okay, and that's
with Packaging, everything?

00:35:13,341 --> 00:35:14,342
Correct. Out the door.

00:35:14,342 --> 00:35:16,611
Um, we sell it to costco
for $9.99.

00:35:16,611 --> 00:35:18,479
Can you get that cost down?

00:35:18,479 --> 00:35:20,348
Uh, if I could
make bigger quantities.

00:35:20,348 --> 00:35:23,518
I can only afford
to make small quantities.

00:35:23,518 --> 00:35:25,520
You're doing great
at costco.
Mm-hmm.

00:35:25,520 --> 00:35:26,788
Have you gotten
into any other retailers?

00:35:26,788 --> 00:35:28,589
I've not
gotten into retail.

00:35:28,589 --> 00:35:30,491
We really wanna
target the box clubs.

00:35:30,491 --> 00:35:32,727
Because what--what they do when
they merchandise our product,

00:35:32,727 --> 00:35:34,696
they put it
in a Coffin freezer

00:35:34,696 --> 00:35:39,300
next to some $180 boxes of
lobster tails and scallops.

00:35:39,300 --> 00:35:40,535
So we--
That's smart.

00:35:40,535 --> 00:35:42,370
They're positioning
just right in there.

00:35:42,370 --> 00:35:43,604
Yes, absolutely.

00:35:43,604 --> 00:35:45,540
Well, it's a actually a platform
for all the ingredients...

00:35:45,540 --> 00:35:47,675
absolutely. Exactly.
Which is even smarter.

00:35:47,675 --> 00:35:50,345
Very interesting.

00:35:50,345 --> 00:35:52,647
Yes, we've actually--
You have a commercial kitchen
doing this, right?

00:35:52,647 --> 00:35:54,415
Uh, we have a...
commercial...

00:35:54,415 --> 00:35:55,683
(Daymond) Co-Packer?
Co-Packer, yes.

00:35:55,683 --> 00:35:57,618
Carole, you obviously
have a great product.

00:35:57,618 --> 00:36:00,688
You're working hard.
It's obviously your life,

00:36:00,688 --> 00:36:02,290
and that's a beautiful thing.

00:36:02,290 --> 00:36:05,360
But in order to take $200,000
from an investor,

00:36:05,360 --> 00:36:07,695
particularly me,
you've gotta be ready

00:36:07,695 --> 00:36:10,264
to take the $200,000.

00:36:10,264 --> 00:36:12,333
I just don't think you're ready
to take someone's money

00:36:12,333 --> 00:36:15,336
and try to scale as big
as you wanna go yet.

00:36:15,336 --> 00:36:16,671
So for that reason,
I'm out.

00:36:16,671 --> 00:36:19,340
(whispers) okay.

00:36:19,340 --> 00:36:20,341
But the gumbo's great.

00:36:20,341 --> 00:36:21,642
Thanks.
I appreciate it.

00:36:23,578 --> 00:36:25,546
I came here because
I need the business acumen.

00:36:25,546 --> 00:36:26,581
I don't have that.

00:36:26,581 --> 00:36:29,250
I just know
that I make a great product.

00:36:29,250 --> 00:36:30,485
And it's a good idea.

00:36:30,485 --> 00:36:32,487
Um, I just--I need help
with that.

00:36:32,487 --> 00:36:34,555
You have decent margins.

00:36:34,555 --> 00:36:36,491
Have you talked
to anybody else

00:36:36,491 --> 00:36:39,360
about giving them
a little bit more incentive

00:36:39,360 --> 00:36:41,295
to make the product?

00:36:41,295 --> 00:36:42,697
Actually, this
particular co-Packer

00:36:42,697 --> 00:36:45,666
is willing to become
the vendor of record.

00:36:45,666 --> 00:36:48,569
What their requirement is
is that I pay for the packaging.

00:36:48,569 --> 00:36:50,471
And I don't
have money for that.

00:36:50,471 --> 00:36:52,607
The packaging
for just that order alone

00:36:52,607 --> 00:36:55,176
is about $10,000.

00:36:55,176 --> 00:36:57,445
But you made
$100,000 this year.
Where'd the money go?

00:36:57,445 --> 00:36:59,347
We're living off of it.
That's all we have.

00:36:59,347 --> 00:37:02,216
We don't have anything else.
I have six brothers and sisters.

00:37:02,216 --> 00:37:04,285
We're all
doing this business together.

00:37:04,285 --> 00:37:07,355
We're crowded up in one house
trying to make it happen.

00:37:07,355 --> 00:37:08,556
Okay. I-I-I got that.

00:37:08,556 --> 00:37:10,291
As an outside investor,

00:37:10,291 --> 00:37:13,628
how can we understand if we're
actually really making money

00:37:13,628 --> 00:37:16,364
or losing money with you?
Yes.

00:37:16,364 --> 00:37:17,498
I need--
I'm so--I'm so busy

00:37:17,498 --> 00:37:19,333
with my guys, trying to
take care of my numbers.

00:37:19,333 --> 00:37:22,170
Okay. I need help
in that--in that area.

00:37:22,170 --> 00:37:23,404
And you will get there...
I definitely do.

00:37:23,404 --> 00:37:26,274
And you're on a great path.
But as of now, I'm out.

00:37:27,341 --> 00:37:30,344
(clicks teeth) okay.

00:37:30,344 --> 00:37:32,513
Any other offers?

00:37:32,513 --> 00:37:36,350
Carole, by asking
for $200,000 for 20%,

00:37:36,350 --> 00:37:37,552
you're telling me
that your business

00:37:37,552 --> 00:37:39,554
is worth a million dollars.

00:37:39,554 --> 00:37:41,422
Yes.
Which it isn't right now.

00:37:41,422 --> 00:37:44,459
I-I... you know,
I rarely get this kind of angst

00:37:44,459 --> 00:37:46,627
in--in the--
in the shark tank,

00:37:46,627 --> 00:37:48,362
'cause I'm very definitive.

00:37:48,362 --> 00:37:50,231
The product
is so fantastic,

00:37:50,231 --> 00:37:52,300
but the infrastructure
isn't there.

00:37:52,300 --> 00:37:54,335
And I know that that's one of
my weaknesses. I definitely do.

00:37:54,335 --> 00:37:56,337
Yeah, it is--It is a problem.

00:37:56,337 --> 00:38:00,141
(Robert) Carole, I, uh...

00:38:00,141 --> 00:38:01,209
I love gumbo.

00:38:01,209 --> 00:38:03,377
If it's on the menu
anywhere I go,

00:38:03,377 --> 00:38:05,513
I order it.
The spicier the Better.

00:38:05,513 --> 00:38:08,116
Okay.
Here's the thing about food--

00:38:08,116 --> 00:38:12,153
the margins
are actually not very good.

00:38:12,153 --> 00:38:16,224
Once you scale, it's a very
challenging business to run.

00:38:16,224 --> 00:38:18,326
'cause the margins
get smaller and smaller,

00:38:18,326 --> 00:38:21,262
and you've really gotta run
a tight business.
Mm-hmm.

00:38:21,262 --> 00:38:22,530
I'd rather see you
take your equity,

00:38:22,530 --> 00:38:28,169
bring in an industry partner who
can guide you to that next step,

00:38:28,169 --> 00:38:29,303
'cause you'll always
find the money.

00:38:31,239 --> 00:38:33,274
I'm out.

00:38:33,274 --> 00:38:37,378
I understand.
I understand.

00:38:48,356 --> 00:38:50,491
Lori, what are you gonna do?

00:38:52,326 --> 00:38:54,095
I think she wants
more gumbo.

00:38:54,095 --> 00:38:57,298
♪♪♪

00:39:03,604 --> 00:39:05,439
♪♪♪

00:39:08,376 --> 00:39:10,378
Three sharks are out.

00:39:10,378 --> 00:39:15,283
Lori and Kevin are Carole's
last chance to get a deal.

00:39:15,283 --> 00:39:16,484
Lori, what are you
gonna do?

00:39:18,586 --> 00:39:19,620
Well, I have to say,

00:39:19,620 --> 00:39:22,490
I love you,
and I love your Gumbo.

00:39:22,490 --> 00:39:24,659
Thank you.
I was not even hungry,

00:39:24,659 --> 00:39:27,295
and my gumbo's almost gone.
(laughs) okay.

00:39:27,295 --> 00:39:29,630
So that's a testament
to your gumbo.
Okay.

00:39:29,630 --> 00:39:33,401
Um, but I'm
kind of on the fence.

00:39:33,401 --> 00:39:37,238
Because $200,000
is a lot of money.

00:39:37,238 --> 00:39:39,240
As Kevin said,
your valuation's at a million.

00:39:39,240 --> 00:39:42,276
And, uh,
that's kind of hard for me.

00:39:42,276 --> 00:39:44,212
I-I-I don't think
you're there.

00:39:44,212 --> 00:39:47,615
This is the smartest thing
I've ever come up with to do.

00:39:47,615 --> 00:39:50,451
It's my life.
It's all that I do.

00:39:50,451 --> 00:39:55,690
Um, right now, um,
I'm homeless.

00:39:55,690 --> 00:39:58,459
I'm staying with friends
right now.

00:39:58,459 --> 00:40:00,294
And when I'm not with them,

00:40:00,294 --> 00:40:03,264
I go over to my sister's house
and stay with them.

00:40:03,264 --> 00:40:06,267
And if not,
I have a Van. (chuckles)

00:40:06,267 --> 00:40:08,236
But...
where does your daughter live?

00:40:08,236 --> 00:40:10,304
She's with me.
She's always been with me.

00:40:10,304 --> 00:40:12,607
And by her being with me
all this time,

00:40:12,607 --> 00:40:14,475
she knows how
to write a business plan,

00:40:14,475 --> 00:40:16,577
she knows how to,
you know, check prices

00:40:16,577 --> 00:40:18,479
on different items
that we use.

00:40:18,479 --> 00:40:20,414
She's, uh,
she's been there for me.

00:40:20,414 --> 00:40:23,351
When I decided
to become a truck driver

00:40:23,351 --> 00:40:25,553
and reinvent myself,
I felt empowered,

00:40:25,553 --> 00:40:29,223
because I was doing
a "Man's job."

00:40:29,223 --> 00:40:31,492
But I was taking care of my baby
at the same time.

00:40:31,492 --> 00:40:35,263
And that's why I'm here,
because I'm here for her.

00:40:35,263 --> 00:40:37,265
This isn't right.
I'll put up half.

00:40:39,467 --> 00:40:42,270
This is crazy.
What do you wanna do?

00:40:42,270 --> 00:40:44,238
She's got a product.

00:40:44,238 --> 00:40:45,339
I know.

00:40:52,146 --> 00:40:53,147
Wow.

00:40:53,147 --> 00:40:54,248
Come in with me.

00:40:58,185 --> 00:41:04,158
So the offer is
$200,000 for 50%.

00:41:04,158 --> 00:41:05,359
For 50%?

